1. The Design (Wireframe)

The page will feature a single, centered card.

Top: Project Title ("PrimaryFeed") and a subtitle ("Database Management Portal").

Middle: Two clear input fields (Email and Password).

Bottom: A "Sign In" button and a footer noting the connection to the GCP backend.

2. React Implementation

This uses standard React hooks (useState) and a mock function for the API call.

3. Connection to the Database Logic

Email & Password: These map directly to the email and password_hash columns in your users table.

Role-Based Routing: The logic if (data.role === 0) handles the specific enum defined in DDL (0=Staff, 1=Volunteer). This allows us to show different pages depending on the database user.

